<theme id="thm223">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Compound time. 8th note tied to next beat (2)</title>
<tocimage>img223.png</tocimage>


<para>In this lesson the next patterns are introduced:</para>

<score>
    <music>
    (score (vers 1.6)
      (instrument
        (musicData
        (time 6 8)
        (n * e)(n * q l)(n * q)(n * e)(barline double)
        (n * q)(n * e l)(n * q.)(barline end)
    )))
    </music>
</score>

<part><title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>

<score>
    <control_play />
    <control_measures />
    <music>
    (score (vers 1.6)
      (instrument
        (musicData
        (clef G)(key C)(time 6 8)
        (n a4 e)(n a4 q l)(n a4 q)(n a4 e)(barline)
        (n a4 q)(n a4 e l)(n a4 q.)(barline end)
    )))
    </music>
</score>
</part>

<part><title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm223_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear: Quarter note tied to 8th
note.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm223_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Train your ear: 8th note tied to quarter
note in next beat.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm223_E3">Exercise 3</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

</theme>

